terizations of HOG can compensate\nfor differences between observed mock data. One example best-case\nparameterization results in an AUC of 0.6 in the F814 filter image with other\nparameterization results equivalent to random performance.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 7 Apr 2017 18:00:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 27 Aug 2019 22:25:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-29"}
